cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Ember and the Long-Horizon Coherence (LHC) Benchmark"
message: "If you use Ember or LHC in research, please cite this entry."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Marques
    given-names: Hugo
    affiliation: Slow Lit Labs
repository-code: "https://github.com/slowlitlabs/ember"
url: "https://slowlitlabs.co"
abstract: >-
  Ember is a foundation model for autonomous agents that operate over
  long horizons. The Long-Horizon Coherence (LHC) benchmark is the
  open eval suite that measures and discriminates models on three
  failure modes — state recall, decision consistency, and workflow
  resumption — across long context gaps.
keywords:
  - autonomous agents
  - long-horizon coherence
  - LLM benchmarks
  - post-training
license: Apache-2.0
version: "0.1"
